-- Wallabies Captain Pocock to Miss All Blacks Game, Needs Surgery
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-08-20T01:34:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-20/wallabies-captain-pocock-to-miss-all-blacks-game-needs-surgery.html
Australia captain  David Pocock  will
miss this week’s Rugby Championship match against  New Zealand 
after injuring his knee in the tournament opener, the team said.  The openside flanker, 24, will undergo surgery tomorrow to
determine the extent of the injury after damaging his articular
cartilage in the first half of the Wallabies’ 27-19 loss to the
world champion All Blacks in Sydney two days ago.  No timeframe was given for Pocock’s return in a
announcement on the Wallabies’  Twitter feed . Wallabies coach
Robbie Deanssaid after the match that scrum-half Will Genia
would take over as captain if Pocock was unavailable.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  